## Operational tier ladder

| Tier | Moment | Command | Scope |
|------|--------|---------|-------|
| 0 — automatic | every `git commit` | lint-staged (auto) | changed files only |
| 1 — structural pulse | after focused edit | `pnpm verify:quick` | types + behavior, cached |
| 2 — integrity sweep | before push | `pnpm verify:parallel` | full static + behavior |
| 3 — artifact synthesis | before significant merge | `pnpm verify:artifact` | static + build shape |
| 4 — CI constitutional | CI gate | `pnpm verify` | full sequential + coverage |
| 5 — operational | E2E / prod validation | `pnpm test:e2e:smoke` | runtime flows |

**Use the lowest sufficient tier. Never reach for tier 4 to answer a tier 1 question.**

---

## Static integrity — what each check owns

| Checker | Integrity domain |
|---------|-----------------|
| ESLint | import boundaries, forbidden patterns, Radix/Base UI confinement, design token usage |
| `typecheck` | main app type graph — RSC, layout, server action contracts |
| `typecheck:test` | test graph isolation — Playwright + Vitest types stay out of app |
| `typecheck:scripts` | scripts graph isolation — seed/AI-gateway types stay out of app |
| knip | dead file surface, unused exports, dependency drift, accidental public API |
| format:check | format contract — deterministic diff surface |
| `lint:agent-contract` | governance file presence, rule strength, forbidden dump dirs |
| `lint:drizzle-journal` | migration SQL ↔ journal parity — prevents silent migration loss |
| `lint:design-contract` | token drift — `@theme inline var(--*)` ↔ `:root`/`.dark` definitions |

The last three (`agent-contract`, `drizzle-journal`, `design-contract`) are **governance checkers** — whole-repo Node scripts, not ESLint rules. They validate doctrine, not syntax.

